The paper proposes a novel method for anomaly detection in complex Cyber-Physical Systems (CPSs) using unsupervised machine learning techniques. Specifically, the proposed method uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to model the system behavior and classify deviant behaviors as possible attacks. This work involves the use of deep learning techniques, which is a common theme in the machine learning community (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with cybersecurity and intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed method involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which is a subfield of computer science (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the modeling of complex systems, which is a common theme in the field of control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the proposed method involves the use of neural networks, which is a subfield of computational neuroscience (cs.NE).
